Solve for the sum of all possible values of $x$ when $3^{x^2+4x+4}=9^{x+2}$. ||| Since we have the equation $3^{x^2+4x+4}=9^{x+2}$, I think we can just solve for $x^2+4x+4 = 9$. This gives us:  
